description: to acquit, settle a debt or dispute
name: *acquitāre

description: ‘collyrium’, powder with which to paint the eyes

description: to be waiting in the woods
name: *imboscāre

description: ‘of a beast’, originally ‘of someone having a spirit’
name: animālis

description: thing with which one is armed
name: armātūra

description: ‘to come to the shore of somewhere’ (literally)
name: *adrīpāre

description: ‘what has been certified’, ultimately from cernere ‘to sift’.
name: certificātum

description: ‘antelope, wild ox’ (phonological shape suggests a borrowing from Oscan)
name: *būfalus

description: days on which accounts were due
name: calendae

description: a plain, piece of flat land
name: campus

description: ‘to change’, possibly from Greek kampein ‘to bend back’
name: cambiāre

description: clan, group of people related by descent
name: clann

description: to give in charge, to let someone give orders
name: commandāre

description: to crawl, scrabble around in earth
name: krafla

description: to be bent like a hook
name: crochir

description: ‘to cultivate’ from colēre ‘to till the soil’
name: cultivāre

description: ‘to cure’, literally ‘to give care (Latin: cura) to’
name: cūráre

description: ‘that which is placed’, from ponere ‘to put’

description: to put a fire or light out
name: extinguere

description: farmer, one who operates a firma or concern

description: flower (of the flour = the finest flour)
name: fleur (de farine)

description: ‘damage’, (literally) ‘what is in conflict with one’s right’
name: iniūria

description: large black kangaroo, a specific type of kangaroo from Northern Queensland
name: gaŋurru

description: to put in order; an order
name: ordināre; ordō, -nem

description: palm tree; palm of the hand

description: plastic, something which can be moulded
name: plastica

description: ‘sheet of papyrus’, possibly of Egyptian origin
name: khártēs

description: one who presides over a meeting
name: president

description: one who is openly for sale
name: prōstitūta

description: to go after, to follow after
name: persequī

description: ‘quail’; possible from Germanic but possibly imitative.
name: quacula/coacula

description: ‘quiet’, literally ‘the state of being put at rest’

description: ‘to shake out again’; from cūtere ‘to shake’
name: *re-excūtere

description: ‘sculptor, one who carves in stone’ from sculpere ‘to scratch’

description: to be fitting, be of repute

description: soldier, one who receives money for service
name: solidārius

description: ‘to surrender’ (Latin super ‘above’, reddere ‘to give back, return’)
name: surrendre

description: ‘to touch, to taste’ (possibly a blend of gustāre ‘to taste’ and tangere ‘to touch’)
name: tastāre

description: ‘temples’, modified form of classical Latin tempora
name: *tempula

description: twist of rope dipped in tar
name: torca

description: ‘to drag behind’ (unattested form of trahere ‘to drag’)
name: *tragināre

description: something which relates to the villa
name: villāticum
